caption: Best food and best service! Highly recommend ordering from here, I think it is the best sushi and udon in all of hyde park. Great vegetarian sushi options too.
Good portions, good food,  great service.

I lived two blocks away from this restaurant for two years before I ever tried it, and I'm so happy I finally did! It doesn't look like much from outside, but the food is very good, unpretentious, and well-priced. Huge fan!
Very fresh sashimi - you do not need any fancy sauces or soy sauce! Excellent service as well!
Would absolutely recommend trying this place. Exceptional atmosphere, delightful food, good customer service. Keep up the good work.
Excellent quality and service.

One of the most authentic Japanese places I have been in the States. The quality and taste has always been incredible, and the service is top-notch. The take-outs were well packaged, and stayed delicious even after a while, even the fried tempura.
They serve big portions and for convenient rates. very friendly staff. Never disappointing.
I love their unagi over rice. Service is unpretentious but punctual. I can't recommend their sushi but their main dishes are above average in quality and taste. Seating is limited.
The customer service is regularly quick, excellent mood, very kind staff. I will visit here again when I arrive here.
One of my favorite places,  great food, and great service! Family owned,  and Excellent food! And continued success and Divine blessings! NAMASTE!
This spot never disappoints. They serve fresh dishes for convenient prices, there are no long waits even when they are busy.
I eat in this spot a lot since I work close by. I got to say the customer service is always great and they keep the place well organized constantly. Prices are fair and they serve generous portions.
Incredible restaurant. Family owned, food is tasty, very fresh, and everything homemade. My favorite restaurant in Hyde Park.
The servers are nice but the sushi is subpar, the soups are decent.  It's a neighborhood joint no frills, it does have byob which is nice.
Typical Japanese restaurant.  Nothing new or outstanding to my appetite.  I ordered a salmon teriyaki to go.  When I opened it at home, they gave me a very dry small salmon tail part.
Pleasant staff, quick service, and the best Dragon Maki roll I've ever had!
It's the cutest little Japanese place ever, the staff is nice, the food is great , and the prices and unbeatable, so affordable,I went there two nights in a row after discovering it.

This is absolutely one of the finest place to eat in the neighborhood. Every time I visit this place I am so happy. They always keep their high  standard service and the highest level of food  they offer. You are always happy with this restaurant. Warmly  recommended.
It our family favorite place. We have been going there for over 20 years. The service excellence and menu is simple but has all the right options.
Great udon and Katsu.  Good lunch specials.
Amazing sushi and unbeatable price, plus the owners and staff are so kind. You can't beat Kikuya
A peaceful hipster dining experience
The food is good and the service is great and friendly.
Wonderful locale, good food, great people, wonderful service.
Amazing to find an authentic japanese place. Looks like a family run restaurant very cosy space

Kikuya can get pricey if you like sushi, but it is well worth the price! It's a family-owned restaurant and they treat you like you're family. We love going! It's an intimate venue and parking is relatively easy. The food is absolutely superb.
I had my first date here and it was really good! I had a donburi ^^
Nice relaxed atmosphere.  Donburi is excellent.
Food was good and plentiful.
Tasty and reasonably priced.
nice to find this great family run restaurant

Run by a wonderful family who makes wonderful food. We eat here a few times a month and love the lunch specials as well as the full dinners. Great tempura, great Katsu and Katsudon. I don't trust a lot of places this far away from the sea to serve sashimi but Kikuya is always fresh and flavorful.
Love Kikuya, the friendliest neighborhood sushi place on the South Side!
This is without out a doubt the best Japanese restaurant in the area, especially if authenticity is important to you.
I ate unagi dong. So delicious. Great service. Reasonable price.
Love this little spot! I always order the chef combo!
Love this restaurant. My husband and I are regulars. We love the food and the people who run the place are the nicest!

Adorable BYOB authentic Japanese restaurant in Hyde Park. Very authentic oyakodon, katsudon, gyudon, etc in addition to the more traditional Americanized options, like various types of sushi and rice. It is small and intimate and perfect for a casual double date. We had a great time and thought everything was delicious!!
The service is never off.  The food is great.  katsu, gyoza, and tempura vegetables make for a very filling lunch for this skinny fat boy.
I love it.  Been going here for years. Favorite is definitely the crazy tuna maki. The miso soup is awesome and the salmon meals are always excellently prepared. Very friendly staff.
Loved it! The food was delicious. It’s a bit small but so cute and cozy
Good Japanese food
Good

(Translated by Google) A Japanese restaurant next to a Korean restaurant. We sell menus of various rolls and rice balls, and sell sushi in the evening. The ingredients are not bad, but the dishes are a bit far from eating in Japan. There is no sauce in tempura or tempura. Maki is not bad, but sushi is just like that.  (Original) 한국식당 옆에 있는 일본식당. 다양한 롤과 덮밥류의 메뉴를 판매하고 저녁에는 초밥도 판매한다. 재료는 나쁘지 않으나 요리는 일본에서 먹는 것과 거리가 좀 있다. 텐동이나 템푸라동에 소스가 없다. 마끼는 나쁘지 않으나 초밥은 그저 그런편이다.
This place is super cute and the service was excellent.  The food was absolutely delicious!
Good raw fish. It brought out my inner grizzly bear.  I spent a lot of money and left very happy.
Always great
Broad variety of dishes and authentic taste.
Fave sushi place

The tempura is terrible... the worst I've ever tried in my life. The Sushi is fine, pretty mediocre. The prices are very low, but if you consider that the food is pretty bad, then it's not cheap, it's accurate "bad food => cheap price", this is not a deal in any way
Tempura is great! Also love the Katsu-Don. Also reasonable price. Love it!
The katsudon and oyakodon are excellent, just like you can get in Tokyo!
Pretty nice food. Love the udon.
Food is generally fine/yeomanlike. I do like their Yu Tofu, as well as their Oyako Don.

I’m only giving two stars for the miso soup and the friendly staff — other than that, the food sucked. Salmon was burnt and inedible, sticky rice too sticky, California roll looked like a child rolled it, and I am 100% certain I heard microwave buttons whenever someone entered the back kitchen to prepare food (the food also came out TOO quickly which warrants suspicion of microwave). Save yourself.
(Translated by Google) The food here is very good Japanese food  (Original) ここの食べ物はとても良い日本食です
Love the Kikuya and Firecracker Maki!!!
Delicious!!!!
Always good food & service
My friends and family took me here because I have the best filters haha
Loveeee this place very nice employees and great food pricing 🤗
Good service but not the greatest food. We ordered  miso soups and a few rolls and it isn't the best.
In my opinion, the only passable Asian food place in Hyde Park (that I've tried of course). A good selection of donburi is the main draw to this place. The prices are fair and great service

I go to Kikuya almost solely for the ambiance. I'm not a big fan of any of their food, it's fine but it's not amazing. The place itself is really cute, colorful and cozy. The people working there are also really nice.
good japanese food.
Great sushi, cozy environment
A hidden gem with a weird but cool vibe. Don't be tempted by sushi because it seems like the right thing to do. Consider the authentic dishes!
Quiet and comfy atmosphere, the food is authenticly great!
Great miso and avocado rolls.
Amazing Byob and lunch specials. Sushi is good and everything else is great. My new favorite spot.
Best unagi (eel) roll I have had in the States.  A great place and the family who runs it are the nicest people around.  When in Chicago, we always come here!
Kikuya is a really nice restaurant to eat a legity japanese food!!!
A small, cute, family-owned place with good Japanese food. A favorite of UChicago students.
Decent BYOB Japanese place
Good Japanese food for a good price. Easily the best in Hyde Park.
Definitely try the ramen.
Salmon butteryyaki is very good

The staff was very friendly and nice. We asked for a special order for our son and they didn't mind to do the favor for us.  Our favorite were Udon noodles. I ordered Niku-Udon, meat was seasoned with soy and sugar (sweet). My son ordered Udon with shrimp tempura. Udon was plain (that I liked, good flavor) and 5pc of shrimp tempura came with it. The tempura were crispy and so yummy!  Of course, they have sushi and Donburi dishes like Katsuya-don, Ten-don etc. I like those Japanese restaurants who have home style Japanese cuisines, not only sushi. I'll definitely come back to Kikuya-san!

This was the best overall food I have ever had in my life.  I've had a few individual dishes that were better, but never a complete meal that could quite compete.  The Hana Chili and Bond Roll were probably my favorite.  Also, the peanut semiretired was amazing.  The service was good but the restaurant was a little cramped and loud.  All forgivable for the taste.

A small and cozy place to enjoy a good time with a friend or two. This is my favorite place to get sushi in the Hyde Park area and It's byob so bring along a bottle of your favorite wine to go with dinner. I wouldn't recommend it for a high profile date night but if you just want a nice casual weeknight dinner, I can't recommend this place enough.
Friendly staff and good food. I like the crispy crab.
Great service and the sushi is nice and fresh.
I've been there twice and enjoyed it a lot both times.
Fresh sushi and good service make this a staple for Hyde Park.

Friendly staff, great food. Try the sushi, the udon, and the miso soup. Salmon butteryaki is not to be missed. The Best Japanese restaurant in the Chicago South Side. And it even gives 10% discount to U of C students.
Great udon and sushi, extremely nice wait staff. And so cheap!

I go here whenever I can, their udon is amazing, and they give you nice portions with sides at a great price. I love their fried vegetables, and the service is friendly, plus they don't charge for delivery.
